  "local_port": 55780,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I uninstall Modified apk by Lucky Patcher (I can only deactivate it)?",
  "response": "Uninstalling a modified APK installed by Lucky Patcher can be more complex than uninstalling a standard app, especially if it has system app privileges or similar properties. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you remove it:\n\n1. **Revoke Device Administrator Access (if applicable):**\n   - Go to your device's **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Security** or **Security & Location**, depending on your device.\n   - Tap on **Device Administrators** or **Device Admin Apps**.\n   - If the app is listed and activated, deactivate it by unchecking the box or tapping **Deactivate**.\n\n2. **Uninstall the App:**\n   - Go back to **Settings**.\n   - Open **Apps** or **Applications**.\n   - Find the modified app in the list and tap on it.\n   - Tap **Uninstall**. If it's only giving the option to deactivate and not uninstall, it might have been installed as a system app, requiring further steps.\n\n3. **Remove as System App (Root Access Required):**\n   - If the uninstall option is unavailable because the app is acting as a system app, you'll need root access to remove it.\n   - Use a file manager with root capabilities (like Root Explorer or ES File Explorer with root enabled).\n   - Navigate to `/system/app/` or `/system/priv-app/`, depending on where the app is installed.\n   - Locate the APK file associated with the app and delete it.\n   - Reboot your device after deleting the APK file.\n\n4. **For Safety and Stability:**\n   - Create a full backup of your important data before attempting to remove a system app.\n   - Ensure you have knowledge of rooting and modifying system directories to avoid causing system instability.\n\n5. **Check with Root Access (if unsure):**\n   - If you suspect the app still exists, use a trusted root uninstaller app to find and remove it completely.\n\n6. **Reset Device (Extreme Measure):**\n   - If all else fails, consider performing a factory reset on your device to remove it, keeping in mind this will wipe all data from your device. Ensure data backup is completed before proceeding.\n\nRemember that modifying apps with tools like Lucky Patcher can lead to software instability and security risks, so it's essential to proceed cautiously.",
